th and send the list with possible amendments to the landlord to negotiate the best deal possible.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section3-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-sign-a-lease-agreement-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Check that the lease is assignable, meaning that you if you decide to sell your coffee shop, the new owner can take over the lease. If the lease is not assignable, the landlord will have the right the cancel the lease agreement, which will negatively impact the sale of your business.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"4","name":"<p>Decide on a coffee shop menu and prepare your finances.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Write down a basic list of all the items you wish to market.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Developing a menu for your coffee shop will play a central part in your business planning. Without it, you won't identify your equipment needs, estimated budget, space requirements, or even location. Spend a good amount of time researching options that will boost sales.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section4-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-decide-on-a-menu-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Calculate your start-up costs.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Starting a coffee shop business from scratch is a sizable investment. The amount of funding you will need depends on your coffee shop's size, food services, location, equipment, and other variables.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section4-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject