/p>\n","text":"<p>Some states don\u2019t require a general business license. However, you need to verify if your location requires specific licenses.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section6-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-check-the-us-small-business-administration-website-for-license-and-permit-requirements-for-your-location-288x288-20200727.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>To find out where to obtain your business license, Google your city\u2019s name and business license.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>In addition, check the United States <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sba.gov\/\">Small Business Administration<\/a> (SBA)\u2019s website for more details.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>In some states, you can simply follow the application procedures laid out on your state government\u2019s website or go to City Hall and request the proper documents.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Apply for a food service license.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>A food service license is issued by your local health department. This specific license will require a health department official to visit your location.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section6-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-business-and-food-service-licenses-288x288-20200814_2023-09-25-004047_cvpm.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>The fees for a food service license are often based on the classification and size of your coffee shop, as well as where it\u2019s located. It may also be based on the number of employees you have. But often the costs range from $100 to $1,000.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>To apply for a food service license, you must fill in the online application or collect an application at your local health department. Once you've filled in the form, submit it and continue the process, which includes a visit from a health department official.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>To ensure your kitchen meets health department standards, view the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.fda.gov\/food\/fda-food-code\/state-retail-and-food-service-codes-and-regulations-state\">different states' rules and regulations<\/a>.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Decide if you need to apply for a food handler's permit.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>If you\u2019re planning on preparing your food in-house, you\u2019ll likely need a food handler's permit to operate. Also referred to as a food handlers certificate, this document will guarantee that your coffee shop meets food sanitation, storage, protection, and preparation regulations.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section6-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-consider-if-you-need-a-food-handlers-permit-288x288-20200817_2023-09-25-004223_spbc.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Your employees will need to complete a state-approved food handler course and purchase a food handler\u2019s permit. Depending on the state you live in, the cost of a food handler's permit can cost $100 to $500. This permit expires over a period of three to five years.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Consider hiring legal representation to help you navigate the legal side of starting a business and obtain the proper licensing and permits.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"7","name":"<p>Set up you business operations.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Choose your business structure.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>In the United States, most coffee shop owners will establish their businesses as LLCs. However, there are a few that are set up as partnerships and corporations. Determine what will best suit you and the type of business you\u2019re trying to build.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section7-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-corporations-and-llcs-288x288-20200622.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Get business insurance.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Obtaining insurance for your coffee business should be considered when planning finances. This step is often overlooked by coffee shop business owners even though it may be required to please banks, property managers, and investors. Ensure your business, employees, and assets are secure by investing in solid insurance.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section7-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-obtain-business-insurance-288x288-20200812_2023-09-25-004410_dcqz.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>General liability insurance is a must-have for any business, especially coffee businesses that have frequent interactions with customers. It will protect you if your baristas, coffee, or any of your products cause harm to people.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Business property insurance will help protect your physical business property. Your insurance should include any outdoor or exterior property such as signage, railings, umbrellas, decks, and lighting.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Business income coverage may depend on your location and coffee business. However, it will help you keep your ability to pay for necessary fixed and variable expenses.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Equipment coverage is critical for your business because coffee equipment is expensive.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Get an Employer Identification Number (EIN).<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Before you start hiring staff, you will need an employer identification number (EIN). Also referred to as the Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN), this nine-digit number will act as a tax ID number.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section7-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-get-an-employer-identification-number-288x288-20200817_2023-09-25-004526_isou.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>To receive your EIN quickly, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.irs.gov\/businesses\/small-businesses-self-employed\/apply-for-an-employer-identification-number-ein-online\">applying online<\/a> is the best option.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"8","name":"<p>Recruit quality staff.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Research local laws and wages first.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Depending on your state, there may be local minimum wage laws to consider. Check with the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.dol.gov\/general\/topic\/wages\/minimumwage\">Department of Labor<\/a> for minimum wage requirements.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section8-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-research-local-laws-and-wages-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>In the United States, the federal minimum wage is $7.25 an hour. However, this can vary by state. Most baristas and coffee attendants get paid the minimum wage of their state and can expect an average income of $19,000 - $30,000 per year.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Research the wages for all positions.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Depending on the type of coffee business you are building, you will need a range of employees to assist you. These may include a barista, waiter\/waitress, busboy, baker, etc. Be aware of the wages each position expects. Some positions might require additional costs because of expertise and training.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section8-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-research-wages-for-all-positions-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Form a payroll budget.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>This will help you to determine the sum total of compensation for your employees. This step may also help you to determine how many employees you can afford to hire.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section8-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-setup-payroll-for-your-staff-288x288-20200812_2023-09-25-004737_hteo.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"4","name":"<p>Place ads in local newspapers and job listing websites.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Starting a business means you\u2019ll be a source for local employment. Advertising in your city will be beneficial to your business and the community.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section8-step4","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-advertise-your-vacancies-288x288-20200813_2023-09-25-004821_yycd.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&