9-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-get-the-right-accounting-software-for-your-needs-288x288-20200723_2023-09-25-011447_lwyo.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"10","name":"<p>Equip and set up your coffee shop.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Bring in the necessary supplies.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Your coffee shop should always be equipped with the proper supplies including paper cups, dispensers, decanters, straws, and napkins. Many of these supplies are indispensable, and you will need them as much as you need a coffee grinder or an espresso machine.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section10-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-bring-in-the-necessary-supplies-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Stock up on utensils.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>If you plan on making snacks and appetizers in-house, you'll need the proper kitchen utensils. This includes cutlery, coffee cups, thermometer, and milk frothers.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section10-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-stock-up-on-utensils-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Basic kitchen utensils can cost between $3,000.00 to $5,000.00.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Invest in the right equipment.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Ensuring that you have quality equipment that works when you need it to will be crucial. Make a list of the equipment you will need and research the different brands and costs.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-coffee-shop#how-to-start-a-coffee-shop-section10-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-invest-in-the-right-equipment-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Automatic drip coffee makers can help you to keep up with demand. It should be durable and able to produce a large amount of coffee per day. Cost for these coffee makers range from $18.00 to $20,000.00.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>A high-quality espresso machine can be quite costly due to material and manufacturing costs, but range from $30.00 to $20,000.00.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>A coffee grinder is vital for a coffee shop business. Most of the time, grinders help with the aroma and taste of your coffee. They may cost anywhere from $20.00 to $9,000.00.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>A refrigerator is necessary for milk, ice, and other cold products and ranges in price from $40.00 to $20,000.00.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>Industrial blenders are a good idea if you are planning on offering a variety of drinks. The craze for frozen coffee drinks is growing and customers will appreciate your business versatility. Blenders range in price from $50.00 to $6,000.00.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"<p>A French press is a popular alternative to drip coffee machines and costs between $10.00 and $5,000.00.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"11","name":"<p>Market your business.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Focus on visual representation.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Invest in quality designs, art, signage, and photography. When you advertise your business on social media, on your website, or in newspapers, make sure you use captivating images. Sell your business by highlighting its beauty and atmosphere.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.z